{
  "answer": "**In Manusmṛti 1.31, the cosmogonic claim is that the creator (the Self-Existent One), for the sake of the prosperity of the worlds, caused the four *varṇas*—the Brahmin, the Kshatriya, the Vaiśya, and the Śūdra—to emanate from his mouth, arms, thighs, and feet, respectively.**[^1]\n\nThis forms part of the broader creation account in chapter 1, where the primordial being produces the social orders as a foundational element of the world's structure.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-13a2db).\n\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 1, [full chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/).",
